modules.description: This module creates a collection of incremental outputs tied to a single input, where selected outputs take specific values and others use a default. It supports operations for selecting one or multiple keys to assign active values, with data types including hashable keys and associated incremental values. Concrete use cases include managing UI focus states and dynamic value assignments in reactive systems.

This module creates a collection of incremental outputs tied to a single input, where selected outputs take specific values and others use a default. It supports operations for selecting one or multiple hashable keys to assign active values, with the rest using a default. Concrete use cases include managing UI focus states and dynamic value assignments in reactive systems.
